Passengers on the Aidamira are waiting for coronavirus test results. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula has announced a total ban on cruise ships entering South African harbours. This is a measure to contain the spread of the coronavirus. READ: Coronavirus: ZCC cancels all Moria events until further notice The ban comes, as more than 1,700 people are quarantined aboard a luxury cruise ship at the Cape Town harbour. Passengers on the Aidamira are waiting for coronavirus test results. READ: SA citizens repatriated from Wuhan test negative for COVID-19 On Sunday, Ramaphosa issued an immediate travel ban on people from high-risk countries affected by the coronavirus. South African citizens have also been advised to refrain from all forms of travel. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Watch the video above for more details. Transport Minister, Fikile Mbalula is updating the country on changes to seaport access.